{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/typeerror-nonetype-object-is-not-subscriptable","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>This error is quite self-descriptive: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">Traceback <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>most recent call last<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  File <span class=\"token string\">\"users.py\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> line <span class=\"token number\">25</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>module<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    user <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> users<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nTypeError<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'NoneType'</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">object</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">is</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">not</span> subscriptable</code></pre></div>\n<p>It means that you are trying to subscript (index) the object that actually is None. In the above example, the <code class=\"language-text\">users</code> list is empty so you can't get the first user from it since None object doesn't define the <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__getitem__\"><code class=\"language-text\">__getitem__</code></a> method. This simply can be fixed by finding out <code class=\"language-text\">Why the list is None</code>.</p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"This error is quite self-descriptive:  It means that you are trying to subscript (index) the object that actually is None. In the above…","frontmatter":{"title":"TypeError 'NoneType' object is not subscriptable","date":"2020-06-17 22:56:36 +0200","categories":["python"],"tags":["python","python3","type-error","list","dict"],"description":null,"keywords":"python, python3, type-error, list, dict","author":"Zoran Pandovski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/c4fa3c5851be4bf4f2f39daf2e691d3b/02521/python.png","srcSet":"/static/c4fa3c5851be4bf4f2f39daf2e691d3b/02521/python.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/typeerror-nonetype-object-is-not-subscriptable","date":"2020-06-17T20:56:36.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/typeerror-nonetype-object-is-not-subscriptable","nexttitle":"Python package download stats from PyPI","nextslug":"/python-package-download-stats-from-pypi","prevtitle":"How to increase Travis CI timeout?","prevslug":"/how-to-increase-travis-ci-timeout","tagList":["java","interface","callbacks","asynchronus calls","python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","bootstrap","web development","data","strings","final","finally","finalize","Git","GitLens","VS Code Extension","CSS","Images","Image Display","CSS Variables","JavaScript","sort","localeCompare","Responsive Fonts","CSS Fonts","default method","static static","plot","spring boot","controller","annotation","mvc","rest","random","List","Set","Queue","hacktoberfest","python3","features","set","hashset"